## Nominal Types (Pillar A)

**Why**: Prevent ID confusion at compile time

```typescript
// Branded types for type safety
type UserId = string & { readonly __brand: 'UserId' };
type PostId = string & { readonly __brand: 'PostId' };
type CommentId = string & { readonly __brand: 'CommentId' };

// Constructor functions
const UserId = (id: string): UserId => id as UserId;
const PostId = (id: string): PostId => id as PostId;
const CommentId = (id: string): CommentId => id as CommentId;

// Usage - prevents mixing IDs
function getUser(id: UserId): Promise<User> { ... }
function getPost(id: PostId): Promise<Post> { ... }

const userId = UserId('123');
const postId = PostId('456');

getUser(userId);      // ✅ Correct
getUser(postId);      // ❌ Compile error - type mismatch
```

## Schema Validation (Pillar B - Airlock)

**Principle**: Validate at system boundaries

```typescript
// Input validation at API boundary
app.post('/api/users', async (req, res) => {
  // Validate with Zod
  const result = UserCreateSchema.safeParse(req.body);

  if (!result.success) {
    return res.status(400).json({
      error: 'Invalid input',
      details: result.error.flatten()
    });
  }

  const user = await createUser(result.data);
  res.json(user);
});
```

## Database Configuration

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### SQLite (Local Database)

**File Location**: `~/.{{projectName}}/data.db`

**Configuration**:
```rust
// src-tauri/src/db/mod.rs
use sqlx::SqlitePool;

pub async fn init_db() -> Result<SqlitePool, sqlx::Error> {
    let db_url = format!("sqlite:{}/data.db", app_data_dir());
    let pool = SqlitePool::connect(&db_url).await?;

    // Run migrations
    sqlx::migrate!("./migrations")
        .run(&pool)
        .await?;

    Ok(pool)
}
```

**Constraints**:
- Single-user database (no concurrent access)
- File-based (portable, backup-friendly)
- ACID compliance with WAL mode
<!-- {{/if}} -->

